Happy holiday to all the men.

5
00:00:09,870 --> 00:00:19,610
So, before you is the schematic of improved version of pulse amplifier for signal generator.

6
00:00:20,070 --> 00:00:23,390
My previous schematic shown here.

7
00:00:24,090 --> 00:00:26,010
Video on it also on my channel.

8
00:00:27,910 --> 00:00:30,650
Why I decided to improve this schematic?

9
00:00:31,410 --> 00:00:36,870
The thing is, schematic itself is very interesting and helps in work.

10
00:00:36,990 --> 00:00:46,210
But it has common point with inductor that drives coil.

11
00:00:47,550 --> 00:00:55,890
If this coil in grenade form, then nothing scary and everything's normal.

12
00:00:56,150 --> 00:01:15,630
But if put Tesla here, then at some operating modes, if you hit the effect, for example, tune frequency and duty cycle of control signals so you hit some harmonic from

13
00:01:15,630 --> 00:01:21,550
wave resonance, you'll see interesting effects.

14
00:01:22,530 --> 00:01:34,510
And with these interesting effects, if power of this key will be about 50 V, you can say goodbye to lab signal generator.

15
00:01:35,510 --> 00:01:42,870
Generally, our experiments for oscilloscopes and signal generators are quite dangerous.

16
00:01:44,010 --> 00:01:56,010
Therefore, to avoid such moment, devices expensive, I developed upgrade of this schematic, which is now shown before you.

17
00:01:58,770 --> 00:02:01,150
So, look at schematic in more detail.

18
00:02:02,150 --> 00:02:07,530
From chips set is same, TC4093BP.

19
00:02:09,030 --> 00:02:18,190
Chip is mediator between lab signal generator and TC4420 driver.

20
00:02:18,930 --> 00:02:29,370
Generally, if you need this schematic to work in continuous mode, this mediator can be removed.

21
00:02:29,370 --> 00:02:44,310
Or if you have a quite good lab signal generator that can output not only pulses with set frequency and duty cycle parameters but also say, cut these pulses

22
00:02:44,310 --> 00:02:49,950
into bursts, then this chip will not be needed for you.

23
00:02:50,070 --> 00:03:01,490
Can directly from such lab signal generator feed to second pin of driver controlling transistor through isolation transformer.

24
00:03:02,950 --> 00:03:06,310
And schematic is thereby simplified.

25
00:03:07,210 --> 00:03:23,290
But I still leave this chip because in practice have to use such moments that lab signal generator is disconnected, say, this node is moved to another place so

26
00:03:23,530 --> 00:03:27,130
there's no influence from Tesla on nearby devices.

27
00:03:28,110 --> 00:03:43,010
And here visible that there are three inputs, one of them common, and two inputs connected to first and second leads of TC4093 chip.

28
00:03:44,670 --> 00:03:50,670
Logical element of this chip is Schmitt trigger.

29
00:03:51,890 --> 00:04:03,070
Its input done with 2-input AND logic, and next happens signal inversion after Schmitt trigger.

30
00:04:03,430 --> 00:04:25,330
So if we use separately output 1 and 2, then can do very interesting thing — when one of generators, say, on logic assembled, sets frequency for us, let's say 100 kHz, feed it

31
00:04:25,330 --> 00:04:35,910
to one of chip inputs, and second generator on logic creates frequency for us, say, 1 kHz.

32
00:04:36,510 --> 00:04:47,590
And this chip with this logic will make for us bursts with frequency 1 kHz, and filling of these bursts will be 100 kHz.

33
00:04:47,590 --> 00:05:04,170
And if these signal generators that control this chip will also have duty cycle, say, of low-frequency generator, then all these parameters this chip will do in form of

34
00:05:04,170 --> 00:05:08,010
bursts and send to control driver.

35
00:05:09,070 --> 00:05:11,170
This very convenient in work.

36
00:05:13,210 --> 00:05:34,190
If you need this schematic to give continuous signal, you unite input 1 and 2 in this little terminal together, and chip transmits unobstructed signal from controlling signal generator

37
00:05:34,190 --> 00:05:35,530
directly to driver.

38
00:05:36,430 --> 00:05:46,470
Here visible that second inversion done to return signal to original as at input, and control transitions to second pin of driver.

39
00:05:48,870 --> 00:05:57,490
Also can note that in this schematic principle implemented that common wire only at controlling part.

40
00:05:57,990 --> 00:06:09,670
That is, united directly driving generator or lab generator, mediator chip, driver, DC-DC converter and power source.

41
00:06:10,270 --> 00:06:13,630
This whole part has common wire.

42
00:06:14,310 --> 00:06:22,450
All other part is absolutely galvanically isolated from controlling block.

43
00:06:23,050 --> 00:06:33,220
This way we prevent through transformer isolation any galvanic connection of controlling block with power part.

44
00:06:35,990 --> 00:06:43,470
Examine this node that does galvanic isolation of controlling block and power part in more detail.

45
00:06:44,210 --> 00:06:48,870
Visible that driver works on inductive load.

46
00:06:50,150 --> 00:06:59,150
To prevent driver shorting directly to common wire, capacitance of 1 µF 50 V included in series.

47
00:06:59,970 --> 00:07:04,410
Also this capacitance removes DC component from signal.

48
00:07:05,410 --> 00:07:15,810
And in series 12.4 Ω resistance added that controls current passing through primary winding.

49
00:07:16,650 --> 00:07:21,610
Next signal from primary winding perceives secondary winding.

50
00:07:22,170 --> 00:07:28,290
Also through same 1 µF capacitance feeds it to transistor gate.

51
00:07:28,290 --> 00:07:45,630
But here we see some wiring that ultimately controls signal form, gives it square form and limits maximum voltage so transistor isn't broken through.

52
00:07:46,610 --> 00:07:53,510
To remove negative component, this UF 4005 diode included.

53
00:07:55,490 --> 00:08:05,770
Instead of this diode, can use other fast-acting diodes, for example, SF, HER and other similar diodes.

54
00:08:07,030 --> 00:08:12,410
Next we see gate discharge resistance 1 kΩ.

55
00:08:12,910 --> 00:08:20,410
And mandatory in this schematic need to use zener diodes connected counter at 15 V.

56
00:08:20,410 --> 00:08:33,330
These zener diodes cut off spikes that can form at frequency changes on secondary winding, thereby protecting transistor gate from breakdown.

57
00:08:34,910 --> 00:08:45,210
As core of isolation transformer that controls power key gate, I took such ferrite ring.

58
00:08:46,150 --> 00:08:51,050
Here I outlined it so its true dimensions are clear.

59
00:08:51,590 --> 00:09:01,910
So, inner diameter of hole 10 mm, outer diameter 20 mm and ring width is 10 mm.

60
00:09:02,590 --> 00:09:04,870
Its permeability mark 2000.

61
00:09:06,250 --> 00:09:18,950
Such ring enough for controlling quite powerful power keys, and can use in this schematic not only IRF series transistors.

62
00:09:19,830 --> 00:09:27,130
If will be available, instead of IRF840, advise to substitute IRF510.

63
00:09:27,590 --> 00:09:32,990
This transistor has gate capacitance only 15 pF.

64
00:09:32,990 --> 00:09:42,280
And IRF510 capable of working at frequencies with proper its control wiring up to 30 MHz.

65
00:09:46,470 --> 00:09:50,410
Into this schematic I introduced terminal block.

66
00:09:51,270 --> 00:10:02,690
Done this so could commute for different schemes of transistor leads and power source.

67
00:10:03,690 --> 00:10:22,630
Say, if we connect on this terminal block minus of key power source with its source, then we get standard schematic where minus for us reaches directly transistor source, and transistor drain

68
00:10:22,630 --> 00:10:34,050
loaded with inductive load that in Tesla schemes is primary winding.

69
00:10:34,770 --> 00:10:52,770
If however we connect on this terminal block transistor drain with plus of power source, then accordingly we get circuit 2 of inductor inclusion, where minus of power source connects to inductor

70
00:10:52,770 --> 00:11:01,710
of Tesla coil, and second end of free inductor connects to source of this key.

71
00:11:02,070 --> 00:11:13,330
Want to immediately note that these schemes behave absolutely differently when working with Tesla coil and show various effects.

72
00:11:14,550 --> 00:11:20,350
Few people know about this and most often this schematic is used.

73
00:11:20,350 --> 00:11:21,010
Why?

74
00:11:21,270 --> 00:11:34,780
Because it's always convenient to put driver, no need for isolation transformer and load is in drain circuit of power key.

75
00:11:36,770 --> 00:11:44,670
And many schemes that some inventors give, draw just, say, key.

76
00:11:44,670 --> 00:11:51,630
But often there specifically this control schematic may be used.

77
00:11:52,910 --> 00:11:55,990
These two schematics work absolutely differently.

78
00:11:56,310 --> 00:12:00,570
And phenomena happening on Tesla coil are different.

79
00:12:01,510 --> 00:12:05,670
This is advice for future experimenters.

80
00:12:05,670 --> 00:12:22,030
And, by the way, want to say that all interesting effects in Tesla coils, and generally in systems we assemble of free-energy generators, manifest only when three frequencies operate in the

81
00:12:22,030 --> 00:12:22,630
system.

82
00:12:23,530 --> 00:12:39,450
Well, let's say, for example, frequency in burst, frequency of burst repetition and third frequency that forms in us, say, in Tesla coil.

83
00:12:40,830 --> 00:12:44,010
Free oscillations, frequency beats.

84
00:12:44,690 --> 00:12:50,570
All interesting effects can be seen only at interaction of three frequencies.

85
00:12:51,450 --> 00:12:58,770
If we just feed one frequency or, say, two, nothing interesting we get from this.

86
00:13:00,010 --> 00:13:16,110
As power source for power key load in this schematic can serve as battery, and inverter connected to battery, which is preferable for raising supply voltage.

87
00:13:16,710 --> 00:13:25,210
And less preferable system, when we power this schematic from lab power source.

88
00:13:25,210 --> 00:13:31,270
This convenient, there is, like for me, regulation from zero to 300 V.

89
00:13:32,270 --> 00:13:38,570
But with such connection to mains can't tune system.

90
00:13:39,550 --> 00:13:46,330
All effects manifest in most cases when we have isolation from mains.

91
00:13:46,930 --> 00:14:06,890
And even if we put filter that's shown schematically here, still can note that during system operation, if we touch hand to key heat sink, we'll feel 50

92
00:14:06,890 --> 00:14:12,690
Hz, this can be felt, despite presence of filtering part.

93
00:14:12,690 --> 00:14:16,850
This brings own corrections to system.

94
00:14:17,850 --> 00:14:35,670
Therefore at precise tunings, especially work with Tesla coils, advise to use specifically power from separate blocks that don't take energy source from mains.

95
00:14:36,670 --> 00:14:39,210
Now examine this filter.

96
00:14:39,850 --> 00:14:42,670
It's shown on board.

97
00:14:44,650 --> 00:15:00,890
These inductive filters can be obtained from old TVs, old power blocks, or wound on yellow rings, homemade.

98
00:15:01,010 --> 00:15:05,350
That is two windings, take two wires and wind in parallel.

99
00:15:06,030 --> 00:15:08,570
Will get analog of this filter.

100
00:15:09,390 --> 00:15:13,750
This is first capacitance value 2 µF.

101
00:15:14,210 --> 00:15:20,310
Next filter itself, then next capacitance 0.68 µF.

102
00:15:20,310 --> 00:15:26,530
Then main accumulator capacitance, it's shown 230 µF.

103
00:15:27,410 --> 00:15:30,530
Values can be in wide limits other.

104
00:15:31,170 --> 00:15:36,510
Main thing voltage was 400 V because feed here up to 300 V power.

105
00:15:37,510 --> 00:15:44,010
In this case capacitances at 200 V, included them in series and capacitance divided in half.

106
00:15:44,010 --> 00:15:53,470
Well and filtering capacitance after electrolytics is 28 nF.

107
00:15:54,150 --> 00:15:59,910
Were capacitors at 2000 V with reserve, but by dimensions they fit.

108
00:16:00,550 --> 00:16:05,230
Nothing complicated in this filter, assembles fast enough.

109
00:16:07,590 --> 00:16:18,410
Here I already on my experienced box acquired last circuit-technical embodiment.

110
00:16:18,750 --> 00:16:21,790
Visible previous holes from work.

